.TH GAUL 1
.\" NAME should be all caps, SECTION should be 1-8, maybe w/ subsection
.\" other parms are allowed: see man(7), man(1)
.SH NAME
gaul-devel \- Development stuff for GAUL
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B gaul-devel
.I "[options] files ..."
.br
.B bar
.I "[options] files ..."
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This manual page might, one day, document the
.BR gaul-devel ,
package, including its API and
examples programs.
This manual page was written for the Debian GNU/Linux distribution
because the original program does not have a manual page.
.PP
.B gaul-devel
is an open-source programming library for evolutionary computation.
.SH OPTIONS
The programs follow the usual GNU command line syntax, with long
options starting with two dashes (`-').
A summary of options are included below.
For a complete description, see the Info files.
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Show summary of options.
.TP
.B \-v, \-\-version
Show version of program.
.SH "SEE ALSO"
GAUL is further documented at http://gaul.sourceforge.net/
